# Global Classes Usage

When generating or editing Astro/HTML, **use variables from `globalClasses()`** instead of repeating Tailwind class strings. Import from `src/pages/api/global/global-classes`.

## Pattern

```astro
---
import { globalClasses } from "../../pages/api/global/global-classes";  // adjust path

const { globalFormLabel, globalCodeInline, globalTextH3, ... } = globalClasses();
---
<label class={globalFormLabel}>...</label>
<code class={globalCodeInline}>...</code>
<h3 class={globalTextH3}>...</h3>
```

## Available Vars (use these, don't rewrite)

| Variable | Use for |
|----------|---------|
| `globalFormLabel` | `<label>` – mb-2 block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 |
| `globalCodeInline` | `<code>` in prose – rounded bg-gray-100 px-1 dark:bg-gray-800 |
| `globalTextXsMuted` | xs muted text – captions, metadata, timestamps |
| `globalFlexRow` | horizontal flex – icon+text, buttons in a row |
| `globalSectionHeaderBar` | card/section header – mb-4 flex items-center justify-between |
| `globalTextH3` | h3/section heading – text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white |
| `globalDropdownClose` | dropdown X overlay – auth-icon-close + absolute inset-0 flex center |
| `globalIconButtonClasses` | icon-only buttons |
| `globalInputClasses` | text inputs |
| `globalFormClasses` | form containers |
| `globalCardStyle` | card/panel containers |
| `primaryTextClasses`, `secondaryTextClasses` | text colors |
| `mutedTextClasses`, `mutedTextSmClasses`, `mutedAltTextClasses` | muted text |

## Combining with extra classes

```astro
<h3 class={`${globalTextH3} mb-2`}>...</h3>
<div class={`${globalSectionHeaderBar} text-sm`}>...</div>
```

Always prefer the global var when the pattern matches. Add only **extra** classes via template literal.
